sorcer.core.context

Class ArrayContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • sorcer.service.ServiceMogram
      • sorcer.core.context.ServiceContext
        • sorcer.core.context.ArrayContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote, Exerter, SorcerConstants, Arg, AssociativeContext, Context, Contexter, Dependency, Domain, Exec, Identifiable, IndexedContext, Mappable, Mogram, Paradigmatic, Request, Scopable, Service, Substitutable

    public class ArrayContext
extends ServiceContext
implements IndexedContext, SorcerConstants
    The Array context has an array like access to a service context. Accessing and setting context values is done via integer indices. Implicit context paths describe i-th element of "array" and are used by the following getters and setters (where: v - eval, c - comment, d - description, i - input, o - output) as follows:
    1. the eval of the i-th element: by v(i) and the setter v(i, obj);
      implicit path: array/[i]/eval
    2. the comment of the i-th element: by vc(i) and the setter vc(i, comment);
      implicit path: array/[i]/comment
    3. the description of the i-th element: by vd(i) and the setter vd(i, description);
      implicit path: array/[i]/description
    4. the input eval of the i-th element: by iv(i) and the setter iv(i, obj);
      implicit path: array/in/[i]/eval
    5. the comment of the i-th element: by ivc(i) and the setter ivc(i, comment);
      implicit path: array/in/[i]/comment
    6. the description of the i-th element: by ivd(i) and the setter ivd(i, description);
      implicit path: array/in/[i]/description
    7. the output eval of the i-th element: by ov(i) and the setter ov(i, obj);
      implicit path: array/out/[i]/eval
    8. the comment of the i-th element: by ovc(i) and the setter ovc(i, comment);
      implicit path: array/out/[i]/comment
    9. the description of the i-th element: by ovd(i) and the setter ovd(i, description);
      implicit path: array/out/[i]/description
